<div data-post-date-group="" data-post-info="">
      <p><span>Published:</span>
        <time datetime="2026-03-13T07:02:58">March 13, 2026, 7:02 pm</time>
      </p>
    </div>
    <article>
      <p>Nathan is at GDC, so this week Gita, Chris and special guest Stella Sacco sit down to talk about the horrors of the video game industry and the joys of <em>Pokopia</em>.</p><p>We don’t need to explain how bad the economy is, or how hard it is to get a job in game development. What happened to Stella Sacco, a 20 year veteran of narrative design, is something else entirely. Stella joined Chris and Gita to talk about <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/stellamsacco_i-didnt-want-to-make-this-post-but-unfortunately-activity-7435120628673900544-ffkG?ref=aftermath.site" rel="noreferrer">her efforts to try to get a development studio to pay he</a>r what she is owed for her work—to the tune of an eyewatering $24,000.</p><p>Later that evening, Stella’s friends, Gita included, ran a fundraising stream to help Stella as she’s still fighting to get paid. If you’re reading this, you missed the Stellathon, but the good news is that they raised close to $13,000.</p><p>To lighten the mood, we rounded out our conversation by talking about <em>Pokopia</em>, a game so delightful it has completely ensnared Chris and Gita. Who knew that taking the best parts of <em>Dragon Quest Builders</em> and mashing them up with <em>Pokemon</em> and adding a dash of <em>Nier</em>’s post-apocalyptic narrative would be so engrossing?</p>
<!--kg-card-begin: html-->

<!--kg-card-end: html-->
<p>You can find this week's episode below and on<a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/7qtlX6MNeEoyNuHBU0chUJ?si=a2f12b75911f43cb&amp;ref=aftermath.site"><u> Spotify</u></a>,<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/aftermath-hours/id1727407094?ref=aftermath.site"><u> Apple</u></a>, or wherever else you prefer to listen to podcasts. If you like what you hear, make sure to leave a review to tell the rest of the hivemind how much you like it.</p>
    </article>

        

      

          

